{
  "texts": [
    "These sensors play a crucial role in smart agriculture by providing valuable insights for precision farming and sustainable agricultural practices (Tasgaonkar et al. 2023).",
    "Agricultural sensors Function of sensors Mechanical sensors Measure soil compaction and detect force used by roots in water observation Optical sensor Measure soil properties, determine organic matters Air flow sensors Measure soil air, soil compaction, and soil type Location sensors Use GPS satellites, to determine latitudes and longitudes Electro-chemical sensor Detect nitrogen phosphors potassium in soil De electric soil moisture sensor Use of electrodes, to measure the dielectric constant of soil.",
    "Table 1 Agritech innovations by trends over time",
    "The field of IoT applications in agriculture encompasses various domains, including precision farming, smart water management, livestock monitoring, and large-scale farming (Palarimath et al. 2024; Yamini et al. 2024).",
    "These applications showcase the potential benefits of adopting IoT in enhancing farming practices."
  ]
}